<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,1374,1975]" pageId="5" pageNumber="346">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,398,1482,1507]" pageId="5" pageNumber="346">Diagnosis. Adult</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[415,485,1482,1507]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="16.[151,263,1838,1861]" captionTargetBox="[154,1436,181,1808]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[154,1439,181,1809]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Belciana spp., adults. 1. B. biformis, male, Sumatra, slide GB / ZSM N 4159 (ZSM); 2. B. biformis, male, Sumatra, slide GB / ZSM N 4160 (ZSM); 3. B. biformis, female, Sumatra, slide GB 7359 (GB); 4. B. biformis, female, Sumatra, slide GB / ZSM N 4198 (ZSM); 5. B. hemodoides, male, Philippines, Palawan, slide GB 7389 (GB); 6. B. hemodoides, female, Philippines, Palawan, slide GB / ZSM N 4286 (ZSM); 7. B. sp., female, Irian Jaya, slide GB 7363 (GB); 8. B. sulawesiana sp. n., male, holotype, Sulawesi, slide GB 7381 (GB)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/241474/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="346">
Fig. 
<number box="[469,485,1483,1507]" pageId="5" pageNumber="346" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
). Wingspan 
<quantity box="[630,714,1483,1507]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.9" pageId="5" pageNumber="346" unit="mm" value="39.0">39 mm</quantity>
. This unknown species is close and similar in appearance to 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Belciana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="346" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="biformis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="346">B. biformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[304,472,1518,1543]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Belciana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="346" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hemodoides">
<emphasis box="[304,472,1518,1543]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="346">B. hemodoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but differs from both by the structure of female genitalia, particularly by shape of antrum and antevaginal plate, shape of sclerotised area in joining of ductus with corpus bursae and by shape of corpus bursae. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[326,527,1590,1615]" pageId="5" pageNumber="346">Female genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[545,633,1590,1615]" captionStart="FIGURES 41 – 45" captionStartId="23.[151,263,1841,1864]" captionTargetBox="[158,1426,223,1811]" captionTargetId="figure@23.[151,1436,193,1821]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURES 41 – 45. Belciana and Diphteroides spp., male (41) and female (42 – 45) genitalia. 41. B. scorpio, Thailand, slide GB / ZSM N 4215 (ZSM); 42. D. kendricki, Irian Jaya, slide GB 7372 (GB); 43. B. biformis, Sumatra, slide GB / ZSM N 4158 (ZSM); 44. B. hemodoides, Borneo, slide GB 7389 (GB); 45. B. sp., Irian Jaya, slide GB 7363 (GB). Most distinctive characters are marked by lines." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/241481/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="346">
Fig. 
<number box="[601,633,1590,1615]" pageId="5" pageNumber="346" value="45.0">45</number>
</figureCitation>
). Ovipositor quadrangular; apophyses anteriores and posteriores ones moderate long and equal in length, rather strong; antrum much narrower than in 
<taxonomicName box="[1053,1177,1626,1651]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Belciana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="346" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="biformis">
<emphasis box="[1053,1177,1626,1651]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="346">B. biformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but broader than in 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Belciana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="346" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hemodoides">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="346">B. hemodoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, strongly split; lateral sides of the antevaginal plate form two acute sclerotised protuberances; ductus bursae longer and broader than in 
<taxonomicName box="[537,662,1698,1723]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Belciana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="346" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="biformis">
<emphasis box="[537,662,1698,1723]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="346">B. biformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[718,883,1698,1723]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Belciana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="346" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hemodoides">
<emphasis box="[718,883,1698,1723]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="346">B. hemodoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; the area in joining of ductus with corpus bursae less sclerotised, but more ribbed and more amorphous compared with two those species; corpus bursae broad, constricted to its caudal part, with prominent extension in caudal part, much bigger than in 
<emphasis box="[1172,1344,1770,1795]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="346">
<taxonomicName box="[1172,1341,1770,1795]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Belciana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="346" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hemodoides">B. hemodoides</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,1374,1975]" box="[199,375,1806,1831]" pageId="5" pageNumber="346">Male unknown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
