<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="347" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,258,1255]" pageId="6" pageNumber="347">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,330,355]" pageId="6" pageNumber="347">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The new species is close to 
<taxonomicName box="[650,775,330,355]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Belciana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="347" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="biformis">
<emphasis box="[650,775,330,355]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="347">B. biformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[833,1000,330,355]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Belciana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="347" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hemodoides">
<emphasis box="[833,1000,330,355]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="347">B. hemodoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, while the ground wing colouration is more similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[329,453,366,391]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Belciana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="347" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="biformis">
<emphasis box="[329,453,366,391]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="347">B. biformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Externally it differs from the last by darker blackish subbasal field, smaller medial and subterminal patches in costal area and by expressed orbicular as white spot and reniform as white spot with black dot. In male genitalia it differs from both species by broader valva, with broader sclerotised part, broader harpe and structure of aedeagus and arming of vesica.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
