<figureCitation box="[437,506,510,535]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="16.[151,263,1838,1861]" captionTargetBox="[154,1436,181,1808]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[154,1439,181,1809]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Belciana spp., adults. 1. B. biformis, male, Sumatra, slide GB / ZSM N 4159 (ZSM); 2. B. biformis, male, Sumatra, slide GB / ZSM N 4160 (ZSM); 3. B. biformis, female, Sumatra, slide GB 7359 (GB); 4. B. biformis, female, Sumatra, slide GB / ZSM N 4198 (ZSM); 5. B. hemodoides, male, Philippines, Palawan, slide GB 7389 (GB); 6. B. hemodoides, female, Philippines, Palawan, slide GB / ZSM N 4286 (ZSM); 7. B. sp., female, Irian Jaya, slide GB 7363 (GB); 8. B. sulawesiana sp. n., male, holotype, Sulawesi, slide GB 7381 (GB)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/241474/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="347">
Fig. 
<number box="[490,506,511,535]" pageId="6" pageNumber="347" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
). Wingspan 
<quantity box="[648,732,511,535]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.3" pageId="6" pageNumber="347" unit="mm" value="43.0">43 mm</quantity>
. Tegulae brown; patagia pale bluish-green, the thorax dorsally between patagia bluish-green like 
<taxonomicName box="[544,671,546,571]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Belciana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="347" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="biformis">
<emphasis box="[544,671,546,571]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="347">B. biformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis box="[730,905,546,571]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="347">
<taxonomicName box="[730,901,546,571]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Belciana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="347" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hemodoides">B. hemodoides</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
Ground colour of forewing pale bluish-green, like in 
<taxonomicName box="[243,374,582,607]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Belciana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="347" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="biformis">
<emphasis box="[243,374,582,607]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="347">B. biformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; subbasal field filled with black-brown, broader and darker than in 
<taxonomicName box="[1211,1343,582,607]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Belciana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="347" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="biformis">
<emphasis box="[1211,1343,582,607]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="347">B. biformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Belciana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="347" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hemodoides">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="347">B. hemodoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; medial field with diffused patches of darker green, and diffused whitish spots; medial line distinct blackish, not reach costal mark, which is less expressed than in 
<taxonomicName box="[906,1034,654,679]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Belciana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="347" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="biformis">
<emphasis box="[906,1034,654,679]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="347">B. biformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[1096,1265,654,679]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Belciana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="347" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hemodoides">
<emphasis box="[1096,1265,654,679]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="347">B. hemodoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; orbicular and reniform stigmata expressed as diffused whitish spots, reniform with blackish dot in bottom; submedial and antemedial lines as diffused row of whitish spots; subterminal line blackish bordered with whitish inwardly; brown apical-subapical patch more contrast and broader, quadrangular, compared with 
<taxonomicName box="[1073,1200,762,787]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Belciana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="347" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="biformis">
<emphasis box="[1073,1200,762,787]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="347">B. biformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, not connected with subtornal brown patch, which is smaller than in 
<taxonomicName box="[709,837,798,823]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Belciana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="347" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="biformis">
<emphasis box="[709,837,798,823]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="347">B. biformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[896,1063,798,823]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Belciana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="347" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hemodoides">
<emphasis box="[896,1063,798,823]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="347">B. hemodoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; terminal line as a row of black vertical streaks; cilia brownish-grey, pale in base. Hindwing dark greyish outwardly, pale greyish-yellow inwardly, with traceable discal spot, medial band and blackish interrupted terminal line with thin whitish bordering; cilia brownish-grey with yellowish-grey.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,258,1255]" pageId="6" pageNumber="347">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,369,942,967]" pageId="6" pageNumber="347">Male genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[384,468,942,967]" captionStart="FIGURES 32 – 34" captionStartId="20.[151,263,1841,1864]" captionTargetBox="[156,1432,196,1814]" captionTargetId="figure@20.[151,1436,193,1821]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURES 32 – 34. Belciana spp., male genitalia. 32. B. biformis, Sumatra, slide GB / ZSM N 4159 (ZSM); 33. B. hemodoides, Philippines, Mindoro, slide GB 7380 (GB); 34. B. sulawesiana sp. n., holotype, Sulawesi GB 7381 (GB). Most distinctive characters are marked by lines." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/241478/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="347">
Fig. 
<number box="[436,468,943,967]" pageId="6" pageNumber="347" value="34.0">34</number>
</figureCitation>
). Compared with 
<taxonomicName box="[668,792,942,967]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Belciana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="347" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="biformis">
<emphasis box="[668,792,942,967]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="347">B. biformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[846,1010,942,967]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Belciana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="347" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hemodoides">
<emphasis box="[846,1010,942,967]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="347">B. hemodoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the new species has somewhat longer uncus, which is more solid than in 
<taxonomicName box="[541,665,978,1003]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Belciana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="347" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="biformis">
<emphasis box="[541,665,978,1003]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="347">B. biformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, broader valva with less developed coremata, wider sclerotised area, shorter and more flat juxta. Aedeagus with dorsal branch of carina bearing very short extension much smaller than in 
<taxonomicName box="[181,348,1050,1075]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Belciana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="347" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hemodoides">
<emphasis box="[181,348,1050,1075]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="347">B. hemodoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; vesica basally bulbous, apically tubular, with 
<number box="[886,927,1050,1075]" pageId="6" pageNumber="347" value="7.0" valueMax="8.0" valueMin="6.0">6–8</number>
small cornuti, irregular tiny cornuti and one separated cornutus, all are smaller than in 
<taxonomicName box="[630,796,1086,1111]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Belciana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="347" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hemodoides">
<emphasis box="[630,796,1086,1111]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="347">B. hemodoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; ventral branch of carina with small patch of tiny spines more dense than in related species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,258,1255]" box="[199,611,1158,1183]" pageId="6" pageNumber="347">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,403,1158,1183]" pageId="6" pageNumber="347">Female genitalia.</emphasis>
Female unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1341,1194,1219]" pageId="6" pageNumber="347" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,258,1255]" box="[199,1341,1194,1219]" pageId="6" pageNumber="347">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1194,1219]" pageId="6" pageNumber="347">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species name is given from the name of the 
<typeStatus box="[883,931,1195,1219]" pageId="6" pageNumber="347">type</typeStatus>
locality, Sulawesi Island, 
<collectingCountry box="[1225,1338,1194,1219]" name="Indonesia" pageId="6" pageNumber="347">Indonesia</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1430,1230,1255]" pageId="6" pageNumber="347" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,258,1255]" box="[199,1430,1230,1255]" pageId="6" pageNumber="347">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,533,1230,1255]" pageId="6" pageNumber="347">Distribution and bionomics.</emphasis>
<collectingCountry box="[540,652,1230,1255]" name="Indonesia" pageId="6" pageNumber="347">Indonesia</collectingCountry>
, Sulawesi Isl. The species was collected in primary forest in October.
</paragraph>
